caption: Chef Nicholas Stefanelli of Masseria (Southern Italian tasting room) and Officina will debut a Greek restaurant in Washington’s Midtown Center in early 2020. The restaurant will highlight the culinary diversity of Greece.  The restaurant, in Fannie Mae’s new downtown headquarters, will import specialty cheeses, wild herbs, and olive oil plus highlight food and wines representing regions from Thessaloniki to the island of Crete.
